<font color="#FF0000">LOOK AT THE RICH GUYS, MOMMIE!</font><br>
<tt>Sat Nov  8 21:15:04 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I don't live in no stinking house trailer... (can't afford the tires...and the concrete blocks!)  Don't drink either..but wish I had an extra beer can...I'd cut the top out with my P-38 and surprise my wife with a flower vase for Christmas.  She's a hard worker and deserves something nice now and them.<br><br>
Never did value people by the type clothes or shoes they wore or what kind of car they drove.  Always admired folks more for what they did while I was looking.. than what they said they had done in the past...or what they were gonna do tomorrow.<br><br>
Don't get me wrong...I do love money!  It comes in great when a homeless veteran needs a winter coat or something to eat.  Don't mind buying a pack of cigarettes for a down and outer every now and then.<br><br>
I sort'a enjoy working cattle...except when some young bull stomps the shit out of me..or some old crazy heifer tries to butt me through an iron gate.  Nobody makes fun of my ragged clothes when I'm out in the hay fields or cutting fire wood.<br><br>
I did feel kinda spiffy in front of Congress in my brand new Wal Mart duds and my re-soled cowboy boots...but I don't want to brag about my finery.<br><br>
Just bought my daughter a pair of tennis shoes to play basketball in...I'm so proud of her achievement on the court that I usually join the rest of the community in overlooking her cheap shoes...kinda lets me off the hook for being..how do you say it in a politically correct manner...financially handicapped...socio-economically depressed Daddy?<br><br>
When I lecture graduate students at several universities (Sorry, none in Arizona) I peek frequently at my $12.95 watch...to make sure I don't run over too far!  The students seem or appear to be impressed by my Wal Mart &quot;Wrangler&quot; watch...anyway they line up to talk to me when I'm finished lecturing.<br><br>
My type of art is Norman Rockwell stuff... not some pile of scrap iron in front of a glass building that costs the taxpayers $60,000!<br><br>
I suppose I'm rich anyway!  I have a good wife and daughter, five dogs (no pedigree stuff) three cats, a rabbit, two ducks, eighteen chickens, four pea fowl and some assorted gold fish that I manage to feed on a regular basis.  I don't know if my family and my critters love me..but the folks at the grocery store and the feed mill sure as hell do!<br><br>
My greatest riches are derived from my Brothers of <br>
Choice who seem to take me as I am.  It's a good thing that I am accepted for no reason..'cause I don't have any extra money to go out and buy it!<br><br>
Now if I had a new trailer house...I might be a little more snootey down at the barber shop.<br><br>
MTF - Making Things Fit
